athi|first=Akshat|last2=Rathi|first2=Akshat|website=Quartz|language=en|access-date=February 9, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|October 1, 2019\n|[[DeepScale]]\n|Develops perceptual system technologies for automated vehicles\n|align=\"center\"| Unknown\n|align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2019/10/01/tesla-acquiring-deepscale-computer-vision-start-up-for-self-driving.html|title=Tesla is buying computer vision start-up DeepScale in a quest to create truly driverless cars|website=CNBC|language=en|access-date=January 3, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|October 2, 2019 (Discovered)\n|[[Hibar Systems]]\n|Advanced automation solutions for small cell batteries through a mechanized pump injection system\n|align=\"center\"| Unknown\n|align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jarratt |first1=Emma |title=Tesla acquires Canadian battery specialist, Hibar Systems |url=https://electricautonomy.ca/2019/10/04/tesla-acquires-canadian-battery-specialist-hibar-systems/ |website=Electric Autonomy Canada |publisher=Electric Autonomy |accessdate=6 October 2019 |language=en-CA |date=5 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n== Philanthropy ==\n* $37.5 million to K-12 STEM education in Nevada.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.insidephilanthropy.com/home/2018/7/26/next-gen-whats-behind-teslas-latest-stem-education-give|title=Next Gen: What's Behind Tesla's Latest STEM Education Give?|website=Inside Philanthropy}}</ref>\n* Multiple contributions of solar power to areas recovering from disasters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.asaproofing.com/2017/10/tesla-philanthropic-side/|title=Tesla's Philanthropic Side|website=asaproofing.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2017/10/25/560045944/tesla-turns-power-back-on-at-childrens-hospital-in-puerto-rico|title=Tesla Turns Power Back On At Children's Hospital In Puerto Rico|website=NPR.org}}</ref>\n*5 million Yuan to Chinese CDC to fight the coronavirus outbreak.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gearprimer.com/automotive/tesla-donates-5-million-yuan-to-chinese-cdc-in-fight-against-coronavirus/|title=Tesla Donates 5 Million Yuan to Chinese CDC in Fight Against Coronavirus|date=2020-01-31|website=Gear Primer|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-15}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Battery electric vehicle]]\n* [[List of automobile manufacturers of the United States]]\n* [[List of Easter eggs in Tesla products]]\n* [[List of electric cars currently available]]\n* [[List of modern production plug-in electric vehicles]]\n* [[List of production battery electric vehicles]]\n* [[Plug-in electric vehicles in California]]\n* [[Plug-in electric vehicles in the United States]]\n* [[NIO]]\n* [[Rivian]]\n* [[Karma Automotive]]\n* [[Faraday Future]]\n* [[Byton (company)|Byton]]\n* [[Fisker Inc.]]\n* [[Polestar]]\n* [[Xpeng G3]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em|refs=\n<!--  <ref name=nytimes>\n{{Cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/03/business/tesla-sales.html\n|title=Tesla Reports Record Output as Elon Musk Achieves Goal |last=Chokshi |first=Niraj |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |date=January 3, 2020 |accessdate=January 5, 2020\n}}</ref>-->\n}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite book |last=Vance |first=Ashlee |title=Elon Musk: Tesla, SpaceX, and the Quest for a Fantastic Future |url={{google books|plain-url=y |id=Yd99BAAAQBAJ}} |date=May 19, 2015 |publisher=HarperCollins |isbn=978-0-06-230126-0}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Tesla Inc.|Tesla, Inc.}}\n* {{Official website|https://www.tesla.com/}}\n** {{Twitter}}\n* {{cite web |url=https://www.tesla.com/blog/master-plan-part-deux |title=Master Plan, Part Deux |first=Elon |last=Musk |date=July 20, 2016 |website=Tesla, Inc.}}\n{{Finance links\n| name = Tesla, Inc.\n| symbol = TSLA\n| sec_cik = 1318605\n| yahoo = TSLA\n| google = TSLA\n| bloomberg = TSLA:US\n}}\n{{Tesla, Inc.}}\n{{Tesla timeline}}\n{{NASDAQ-100}}\n{{Automotive industry in the United States}}\n{{Trucking industry in the United States}}\n{{